////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////Stateless and statefulless.

This is a very common interview question in Web API / .NET / system design.
1️⃣ 5-Year-Old Explanation
Imagine a shop.
🟢 Stateful
You go to the shop today and say:
“Remember me? I came yesterday.”
The shopkeeper remembers you and your previous order.
That is stateful.
🔵 Stateless
You go to the shop and every time you must say:
“My name is Abhishek and I want pizza.”
The shopkeeper does not remember anything from previous visit.
That is stateless.
2️⃣ Simple Technical Definition
🔹 Stateless
A stateless system does not store information about previous requests. Every request is independent.
Example: Web APIs.
Each request must contain all required information.
🔹 Stateful
A stateful system stores information about previous interactions.
Example: Applications that maintain session data.
3️⃣ Example in Web Applications
Stateless Example
REST API in **ASP.NET Core.
