7️⃣ Perfect Interview Answer
You can say:
In ASP.NET Core Web API, when a request comes from the client, it first reaches Program.cs where the application and middleware pipeline are configured. The request then passes through middleware components like authentication and authorization, after which routing determines the correct controller and action method. The controller processes the request and sends the response back to the client.
